        "is_accepted": true,
        "last_activity_date": 1524056695,
        "creation_date": 1524028158,
        "body": "<p>You can use the <a href=\"http://checkstyle.sourceforge.net/config_coding.html#IllegalTokenText\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">IllegalTokenText rule<\/a>.\nInclude the following inside the  tag to mark the violation of this rule as error:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;property name=\"severity\" value=\"error\"/&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Full example:\n    \n    <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;module name = \"Checker\"&gt;\n    &lt;property name=\"charset\" value=\"UTF-8\"/&gt;\n    &lt;property name=\"severity\" value=\"warning\"/&gt;\n    ...\n    &lt;module name=\"TreeWalker\"&gt;\n        ...\n        &lt;module name=\"IllegalTokenText\"&gt;\n            &lt;property name=\"severity\" value=\"error\"/&gt;\n            &lt;property name=\"tokens\" value=\"STRING_LITERAL\"/&gt;\n            &lt;property name=\"format\" value=\"abc|xyz\"/&gt;\n            &lt;property name=\"ignoreCase\" value=\"true\"/&gt;\n        &lt;/module&gt;\n        ...\n    &lt;/module&gt;\n&lt;/module&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Which generates the following error:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Token text matches the illegal pattern 'abc'. [IllegalTokenText]\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
